    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The trial of the first of 10 suits\nagainst the Northern Pacific rail-\nway for aggregate damages amount\ning to nearly $4,000, was called to-\nday in Judge Sullivan's court.\n\n\nThe cases grow out of the forest\nfires at Ponderay, Idaho. last Au-\ngust, which it is alleged were start\ned through fires lighted by men\nemployed in clearing ground by the\nrailroad.\n\n\nThe first case called was that OF\nc. F. Ewing & Co. for damages in\nexcess of $1,000. Eighty-seven\nwitnesses have been called and the\ntrial will consume seven or eight\ndays, 1t is thought."
    }
